comments: Mann (OKC) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Gordon (DEN) is retreating his arm when he lightly brushes Giddey's (OKC) right arm and marginal contact occurs after the gather during the driving shot attempt.
Giddey (OKC) lowers his arm down and makes contact with Gordon's (DEN) left arm that affects Gordon's power up to the basket.
Murray (DEN) legally contests Dort's (OKC) driving shot attempt at the basket.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as the players both briefly engage before separating after the pick.
Dort (OKC) briefly gets his hand tangled up with Jokic (DEN) before separating on the pick.
Muscala (OKC) lowers his left arm down and makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) left arm during his shot attempt at the basket.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes one step before releasing his pass.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) establishes himself in Murray's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs as the player's come together.
Jokic (DEN) lowers his arm down and makes contact with the ball, dislodging it from Dort's (OKC) grasp after his gather into a driving shot attempt.

Dort (OKC) reaches his right arm in and makes arm contact with Jokic (DEN) that causes Jokic to lose control of the ball. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) moves laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and makes body contact, affecting his SQBR.
Muscala (OKC) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Muscala (OKC) is firming up on his left foot and marginal contact occurs as Caldwell-Pope (DEN) fights over the top of the pick.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot and proceeds to slide that foot as he moves in the lane.
Gordon (DEN) gets to ball height and makes contact with the ball that deflects Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
After the timeout, Denver is whistled for a delay of game.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) reaches in and makes contact with Muscala's (OKC) lower body, which affects his SQBR prior to making the pass.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) commits a take foul on Gordon (DEN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) slides across Giddey's (OKC) front and his left arm comes across Giddey's face during the driving shot attempt.
Bazley (OKC) commits a take foul on Murray (DEN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Murray (DEN) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) come together at the same spot on the floor and marginal contact occurs as the offensive player releases from the contact.
Gordon (DEN) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Giddey (OKC) commits a take foul on Jokic (DEN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Braun (DEN) gets to ball height and cleanly blocks Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
